cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as multi-person part segmentation and human pose estimation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel technique that takes advantage of synthetic data, which is a common topic in machine learning research, particularly in the sub-category of generative models (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of auxiliary tasks to bridge the gap between synthetic and real data, which is a common topic in the sub-category of multi-task learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of real-world datasets such as Pascal-Person-Parts and COCO-DensePose, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
